1. HIGH - TAP interface missing bridge association (line 49-53): The microvm.interfaces entry defines a tap device but doesnt specify which bridge to attach it to. Without this, the VM has no network connectivity. Fix: add bridge = "br-reel" to the interface definition:
   interfaces = [{
     type = "tap";
     id = "vm-reel-0";
     mac = "02:00:00:00:01:01";
     bridge = "br-reel";
   }];

2. HIGH/Security - Secrets need owner set (lines 82-89): The agenix secrets default to root ownership but the reel-life service runs as a dedicated user. Fix: add owner = "reel-life" to both secret definitions.

3. MEDIUM - Empty allowed users list (line 99): With chatTelegramAllowedUsers = [] and chatTelegramChatID = 0, the bot may ignore all messages including the first one needed for auto-capture. Add a better comment explaining the behavior. Check the reel-life flake input to understand how the allowedUsers list works when empty.

After fixing, verify the Nix expressions parse: run nix-instantiate --parse on the changed file.
